		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Oct 5 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser D D</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">On opening your<lb/> last No. of the Oc. I find an article<lb/> respecting a <persName>Mr. E. Marcussohn</persName>&#44; ac&#45;<lb/>companied by a letter purporting to be<lb/> written by him to the Editor of the Jew&#45;<lb/>ish Chronicle of <placeName>New York</placeName>. Affecting to<lb/> deny the statement made in the <date>August</date><lb/> No. by <persName>Rev J C. Davis</persName> of <placeName>Montgomery</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Allow me to say here is disclosed<lb/> a curious affair. In the first place<lb/> no letter like that in your paper was<lb/> ever received by the Editor of the Jewish<lb/> Chronicle&#44; that is curious and in<lb/> the second place&#44; either <persName>Mr E. Marcussohn</persName><lb/> was or was not the person that presided<lb/> over the Jewish congregation in <placeName><sic>montgom<lb/>ery</sic> Ala.</placeName> and to whom reference is made<lb/> in the <date>Aug</date> No of the Jewish Chronicle<lb/> If he is&#44; then I shall undertake to prove<lb/> to the Jewish and Christian public the<lb/> following facts from indisputable evidence</p>
			<p>1. That he sought instruction of our mis&#45;</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>ionary in <placeName>Montgomery</placeName> and of the respected clergy<lb/> men there of his own accord that on the<lb/> <date>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of July</date> last in the presence of a number<lb/> of his people he publicly declared his conviction<lb/> that <persName>Jesus</persName> of <placeName>Nazareth</placeName> was the messiah&#8212;that<lb/> whereupon his people become furious and<lb/> refused to pay him his just claim and that<lb/> he was obliged to leave his home and that<lb/> he found an asylum with <persName>Rev Mr Oliver</persName><lb/> a Christian minister&#8212;who also advanced<lb/> him &#36;70 to pay his debt among his<lb/> people. That <del>he</del> it was generally known<lb/> in <placeName>Montgomery</placeName> that he had <sic>publically</sic> ab&#45;<lb/>jured Judaism and embraced Christian&#45;<lb/>ity. That on application by his friends for aid the<lb/> society offered him a liberation as miss&#45;<lb/>ionary to the Jews that he accepted at<lb/> that he went to <placeName>Charleston</placeName> had an interview<lb/> with <persName>Rev Mr Bernheim</persName>&#8212;received through<lb/> him from the Treasurer his salary for<lb/> <date>August</date> and <date>September</date>. That he was located<lb/> in a city not far from <placeName>Charleston</placeName>&#8212;<lb/> or else if he is the same man. One or both<lb/> of us have been deceived in the person. Either<lb/> <persName>Mr Marcussohn</persName> &#40;or <persName>Markesson</persName>&#41; from <placeName>Mont&#45;<lb/>gomery</placeName> <add>&#63;</add> C. <placeName>South Carolina</placeName> was not<lb/> the minister of the Jewish cong in <placeName>Mont&#39;ry</placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>or else the man that called on you and<lb/> whom you represent to be such&#44; was not.<lb/> Now if he be not <persName>Mr Marcussohn</persName><lb/> mentioned in the Jewish Chronicle<lb/> a game is commenced in your paper<lb/> at which I am resolved to expose.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You or <persName>Mr Marcussohn</persName> is in a terri&#45;<lb/>ble dilemma. Either he has been guilty<lb/> of moral enormities which render him<lb/> unworthy of the confidence of any man<lb/> or else there is unblushing inequity<lb/> on your part. In either case I<lb/> shall not spare nor give any quarter.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Either he has been attempting to impose<lb/> upon the christian community or else<lb/> you are attempting to impose upon Jewish<lb/> community.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">You have fairly begun<lb/> a difficulty which I shall take care<lb/> you do not escape&#44; or else he has&#44;<lb/> the whole matter will be brought<lb/> to an issue very shortly.</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">I remain yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">ElRm Gregor<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
			<p>I do not intent this for publication but to<lb/> show you how matters stand&#8212;the truth most come<lb/> out</p>
          
